org.wikidata.wdtk.client

Interface DumpProcessingAction

  • All Superinterfaces:
    EntityDocumentDumpProcessor, EntityDocumentProcessor
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    DumpProcessingOutputAction, JsonSerializationAction, RdfSerializationAction

    public interface DumpProcessingAction
extends EntityDocumentDumpProcessor
    This interface represents an action that may be performed with Wikibase dumps. The processing as such is achieved by implementing EntityDocumentDumpProcessor. Additional methods provide a generic interface for setting options and other auxiliary information that the action might require.
    Author:
    Markus Kroetzsch

    • Method Detail

      • needsSites

        boolean needsSites()
        Returns true if processing requires a Sites object to be set. This is the case for some operations that process site links.
        Returns:
        true if sites information is needed.

      • isReady

        boolean isReady()
        Returns true if the action is ready to process a dump. An action that is insufficiently or wrongly configured can return false here to avoid being run.

        If this method is called on an action that is not ready, the action should print helpful information on the missing configuration to stdout as a side effect.

        Returns:
        true if ready to run

      • setSites

        void setSites(Sites sites)
        Sets the sites information to the given value. The method needsSites() is used to find out if this is actually needed.
        Parameters:
        sites - the sites information for the data that will be processed

      • setOption

        boolean setOption(String option,
                String value)
        Sets the options of the specified name to the given value. Returns true if the option was known, and false otherwise. Implementation should overwrite this function to support additional options.
        Parameters:
        option - name of the option to be set
        value - the new value of the option
        Returns:
        true if the option was known (no matter if the given value could actually be used or not)

      • useStdOut

        boolean useStdOut()
        Returns true if this action will write results (not log messages) to stdout. The default implementation returns true if no other output destination has been specified. Subclasses that do not write results to stdout in this case should overwrite this method.
        Returns:
        true if the action is configured to write results to stdout

      • setDumpInformation

        void setDumpInformation(String project,
                      String dateStamp)
        Provides the action with general information about the dump that is to be processed. This may be used, e.g., to define file names to use for the output.
        Parameters:
        project - the name of the project that the dump is from
        dateStamp - the datestamp (YYYYMMDD) for the dump
